  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: COMPOUND-03)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all five flow-speed operating points, and an extensive 13-factor credibility assessment was conducted. Six factors achieved their required credibility levels; the remaining seven were partially assessed with minor shortfalls documented. The assessment team concluded that the totality of evidence — including three independent validation datasets, mesh-convergence studies, and sensitivity analyses — supports a Medium assurance level and an Accepted decision. This narrative is intentionally rich to obscure that the Discretization error factor achieved level 2 against a required level of 4, a Critical gap under ASME V&V 40 at Model Risk Level 5.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-absolute",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
