      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with regression test suite; all critical tests passing prior to simulation execution.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 was used under a validated QMS. Full regression suite (847 tests) passed. Software version and build hash recorded in simulation log. SQA level 3 achieved and meets required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) or equivalent order-of-accuracy test demonstrating expected convergence rates for governing equations.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification was performed on the Navier-Stokes and species transport (hemolysis) equations. Observed convergence rates matched theoretical second-order accuracy within 4%. Code verification level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based grid convergence index (GCI) reported for hemolysis index QoI on at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI < 5% on finest mesh.",
      "rationale": "A two-mesh refinement study was conducted (coarse: 4.2M cells; medium: 9.8M cells). Richardson extrapolation was not performed due to absence of a third systematically refined mesh. GCI could not be formally computed; estimated discretization uncertainty is 12–18% based on medium-to-coarse comparison. This falls short of the three-mesh extrapolation requirement. Achieved level 2 against required level 4. The assessment team noted this gap but characterised it as acceptable given the conservative uncertainty bounds applied in the Monte Carlo UQ step, and elected to proceed with an Accepted decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions replicated in simulation to within ±5% of measured values; fluid temperature, viscosity, and hematocrit documented.",
      "rationale": "All five operating points were replicated. Inlet flow rates matched to ±2.3%, rotational speed to ±0.4 RPM. Hematocrit (35%) and plasma viscosity documented and matched in CFD. Test conditions level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric (e.g., E% or validation uncertainty) computed for hemolysis index across all operating points; systematic bias characterised.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute error in hemolysis index was 11.4% across five operating points. Validation uncertainty was computed per ASME V&V 20. Systematic over-prediction bias of +8% identified and documented. Achieved level 3 falls one gradation below required level 4; gap acknowledged in uncertainty budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (hemolysis index) directly maps to the clinical endpoint; no surrogate quantities used.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) computed directly from the power-law hemolysis model integrated over Lagrangian particle trajectories. NIH is the regulatory-accepted clinical surrogate for hemolysis risk. QoI relevance level 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments performed on the same device geometry at overlapping operating conditions; blood analogue fluid properties within 10% of clinical values.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic pump geometry (identical to COU geometry). Two of five operating points were within the clinical VAD range; three were extrapolated. Blood analogue viscosity was within 8%. Achieved level 3 against required level 4; extrapolation range noted as minor gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence to residual tolerance ≤ 1e-6 for all equations; mass imbalance < 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to residuals ≤ 1e-7. Mass imbalance was < 0.003% across all operating points. Solver error level 3 achieved and meets required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup, boundary condition assignment, and post-processing scripts by a qualified analyst not involved in primary simulation.",
      "rationale": "An independent CFD analyst reviewed mesh topology, boundary condition files, and post-processing scripts. Two minor discrepancies in outlet pressure specification were identified and corrected prior to final runs. Use error level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis power-law coefficients justified by literature comparison; sensitivity of hemolysis prediction to model form documented.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on literature consensus for rotating blood pump flows. Hemolysis power-law coefficients (Giersiepen et al.) used; sensitivity to alternative coefficients (Zhang et al.) evaluated showing ±15% variation. Model form level 3 achieved; coefficient uncertainty is a recognised limitation at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain input parameters identified; probability distributions assigned and propagated via Monte Carlo UQ; Sobol sensitivity indices computed.",
      "rationale": "Fourteen uncertain input parameters identified (fluid viscosity, density, pump speed tolerance, inlet flow distribution, hemolysis model coefficients, wall roughness). Beta and normal distributions assigned from literature. 10,000-sample Monte Carlo propagation performed. Sobol first-order and total-order indices computed. Model inputs level 4 achieved and meets required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Minimum of three independent experimental replicates per operating point; inter-laboratory reproducibility demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro hemolysis measurements were performed in duplicate (n=2) at each of the five operating points within a single laboratory. Inter-laboratory reproducibility data were not available. Achieved level 2 falls below required level 3; the assessment team accepted this gap on the basis that duplicate measurements showed < 5% coefficient of variation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Geometric fidelity of simulation domain to physical test article confirmed; CAD-to-mesh deviation < 0.1 mm in critical flow regions.",
      "rationale": "CT scan of the physical test pump was compared to the CAD geometry used for meshing. Maximum deviation in impeller blade region was 0.07 mm; volute deviation < 0.05 mm. Equivalency of input parameters level 3 achieved and meets required level."
    }
